&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Adult Mental Health Services &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Intensive Rehabilitation Service&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;COOK/HOUSEKEEPER Permanent post&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: Forest Close&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band:        Band 2 £17,652 - £19,020 pa pro rata (dependent on experience)  &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours:      37.5hrs per week (flexibility required able to work between the hours of 7am-6pm including weekends and Bank Holidays&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Post Ref:  457-20-020-AN&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Forest Close is a 30 bedded Intensive Rehabilitation and Recovery Unit, which aims to deliver high quality, effective rehabilitation and recovery to individuals whose needs cannot currently be met by less intensive mainstream Adult Mental Health Services.&lt;br /&gt;We are looking to recruit a reliable and conscientious person to join the housekeeping service based at Forest Close. &lt;br /&gt;Are you well motivated, have a good sense of humour and able to work flexibly. Do you have a desire to work with clients who have a complex mental health problem.&lt;br /&gt;Duties will include providing a cleaning service to maintain high standards of cleanliness and the cooking of patient’s meals. Cleaning duties will be undertaken in line with work schedules and catering duties in line with food hygiene regulations and practices. Possession of a basic food hygiene certificate is Essential, as is previous experience of providing cleaning/catering services. &lt;br /&gt;The successful applicant will be expected to work on his or her own initiative as well as working as part of a team&lt;/p&gt;
